Quantifying Nucleation Events

TeMpSA
March 15, 2017

Background

  • Currently Chiwoo Park of FAMU analyzes (S)TEM data produced by Nigel et al. including

    • Layla's 2015 Nano Letters paper
    • Several Patricia Abellan papers

  • Unfortunately software to implement these methods isn't publicly available

  • One that we have been able to implement is the robust regularized SVD approach described in Vo and Park (2017)

Method overview

  • Each frame (Y) is decomposed into background (B), foreground (F) and noise (E)

\[ Y = B + F + E, \]

Appraoch

  • Robust regularlized SVD (RobRSVD; Zhang et al. 2013) is used to estiamte background

  • A sparse modification of RobRSVD is used to estimate foreground

  • The degree of smoothness is automatically chosen via GCV

  • The RobRSVD R library implements standard RobRSVD in pure R

  • We translated the RobRSVD package into C++ and added the option to sparseify

Example

  • Synthetic data example from Vo and Park (2017)

Real data example

  • Real data is much messier
  • Consider nucleation data from Abellan et al.

Issue 1: Anode

  • Doesn't generalize well to anode videos.

Issue 2: Missing Data

  • Doesn't perform well when data are missing (75% missing here)
